# /etc/fstab entries for BlossomFS
#
# BlossomFS does not support direct fstab mounting (it requires a
# userspace daemon). Use systemd or an init script instead.
#
# Option 1: systemd template service (recommended)
#
#   1. Copy contrib/blossomfs@.service to /etc/systemd/system/
#   2. Copy contrib/blossomfs.toml.example to /etc/blossomfs/blossomfs.toml
#   3. Enable and start:
#
#       sudo systemctl enable blossomfs@/mnt/blossom.service
#       sudo systemctl start blossomfs@/mnt/blossom.service
#
# Option 2: /etc/fstab with a helper script
#
#   Add a line like this (requires a mount.blossomfs helper script):
#
#   /etc/blossomfs/blossomfs.toml  /mnt/blossom  fuse.blossomfs  defaults,config=/etc/blossomfs/blossomfs.toml  0  0
#
#   The helper script (mount.blossomfs) would need to be placed in /sbin/
#   and wrap the blossomfs binary.
